---
name: scljet-write-index-text
description: SclJet index writer on a TEXT column — BINARY-collation index B-tree that reference SQLite validates and uses (cross-backend)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet text-column index

[ByteSlice, byteSliceToList, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableWithIndexDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)

```scalascript
// Index on a TEXT column with out-of-order and duplicate values. Entries sort by
// (name, rowid) in BINARY order; reference integrity_check validates the index and
// the query planner uses it. int and JS agree.
val rows = List(
  List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("carol")),
  List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("alice")),
  List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("dave")),
  List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlText("bob")),
  List(SqlInteger(5L), SqlText("alice")))

buildTableWithIndexDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(id INTEGER, name TEXT)",
  "byname", "CREATE INDEX byname ON t(name)", List(1), rows) match
  case Right(bytes) => println((bytes.length / 512).toString + ":" + byteSliceToList(bytes).toString)
  case Left(error) => println("ERROR:" + error.message)
```
